A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Part 3 of Article 7 of Chapter 3 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to the Georgia Student Finance Authority, so as to provide for tuition
3 grants to children and spouses of certain public employees killed or permanently disabled in
4 the line of duty; to provide for charitable contributions to the Georgia Student Finance
5 Authority for such grants; to expand eligibility for the Public Safety Memorial Grant to
6 provide for tuition grants to children and spouses of emergency medical technicians,
7 firefighters, highway emergency response operators, law enforcement officers, and prison
8 guards who are killed or permanently disabled in the line of duty; to provide for tuition grants
9 to children and spouses of public school employees and public school teachers who are killed
10 or permanently disabled by an act of violence in the line of duty; to provide definitions; to
11 provide for maximum grant amounts; to provide for eligibility; to provide for an application
12 process; to provide for grant renewals; to provide for rules and regulations; to provide for
13 related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
